<HL>
   Technology Brief -- Energy Conversion Devices Inc.:
   Alliance Is Set With Canon
   To Build Solar Cells in U.S.
</HL>
<DATE>
07/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ENER CANNY WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   Energy Conversion Devices Inc., Troy Mich., said it has
agreed to form a joint venture with Canon Inc. of Japan to
manufacture solar cells in the U.S.
   Canon is making an initial $30 million capital
contribution to the joint venture, including a credit of $8
million for canceling a term loan to Energy Conversion
Devices. Energy Conversion Devices is contributing its solar
manufacturing plant and a technology license.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Eliichi Kondo, chief executive of Canon's chemical
products operations, will be president and chief executive
officer of the joint venture.
</TEXT>
